result.execSummary:
The defendant Megan M Sjostrom was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manuf/Deliver Schedule I, II Narcotics, a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Pay court costs.   **NOTE: THE DEFENDANT IS ORDERED TO PAY ALL COURT OBLIGATIONS TO THE CLERK OF COURTS OFFICE.   Payment is due within 30 days. -------------------------------

No alcohol.   No illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia. No prescribed medication without a valid prescription.
-------------------------------

Reimburse Walworth County Drug Enforcement Unit in the amount of $100.00 for "buy money."
Counseling as recommended by Probation Agent.   Provide biological specimen to state crime lab for DNA analysis, and pay DNA analysis surcharge.   The defendant must pay Department of Corrections Supervision fees.
-------------------------------

AODA assessment and follow through with recommendations.
-------------------------------

timeConds.notes:
Five (5) months in the Walworth County Jail with work release privileges. Court STAYS all but THIRTY (30) days. Conditional jail time may be served in Brown County under electronic monitoring if she is otherwise eligible for it in Brown County. JAIL TURN IN DATE: On or before July 26, 2016 at 8:00 a.m.
-------------------------------
The defendant is to complete a total of twenty hours of community service work during EACH year of probation ordered to a total of sixty (60) hours of community service work.
